2000-12-24  perdig  <perdig@users.sourceforge.net>

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/callbacks.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/combat.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/combat.h, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/dlg_options.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/dlg_options.h, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/game.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/map.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/map.h, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/TODO:
	- Added a ARMY(OPTIONS, TYPE) macro to combat.h to avoid the need to type
	  OPTIONS->ARMY[OPTIONS->NUMBER][TYPE]. It is used to get the default number of
	  units of this type for this map
	- Fixed a lot of bugs
	  - No more GTK error messages
	  - No more "Your client must be updated" messages

	* /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/combat.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/combat.h, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/dlg_options.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/game.c, /cvsroot/ggz/ggz/game_clients/combat/TODO:
	- All the options checking stuff is in the combat_options_check function in
	  combat.[ch]
	- combat_options_string_read now makes a copy of the options string passed, so
	  that it can be used after the call
	- Uses the combat_options_check function to check if it should send the current
	  options to the server. If it can't, tells the user what has gone wrong (and
	  doesn't erase the map)

